You&#39;d replace the ARCWriterProcessor with a processor that wrote instead 
to a database rather than to disk.  Study this module to see how it 
works (Also see the developer&#39;s manual on writing processors).

Currently title, description and keywords are not extracted but it 
shouldn&#39;t be hard to amend the ExtractorHTML, a processor that runs 
earlier than ARCWriterProcessor in the processing chain, so it extracts 
this metadata.  Its already reading META headers to see if crawling is 
barred by a robots META-tag so keywords and description should be 
straight-forward.  For title, you&#39;d have to add a special case to the 
RELEVANT_TAG_EXTRACTOR regex.   Your extraction-additions would write 
the discovered metadata into the &#39;cart&#39; that gets passed down along the 
processing chain, the CrawlURI.   This laden CrawlURI will be passed 
into your db writer (CrawlURI is where you get the pointers to the 
downloaded content).

